   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL THREE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE TYPES IN THE OLD TESTAMENT LESSON FOUR THE ARK AND THE GOOD LAND OUTLINE The ark typifying Christ as the salvation of God s elect: The redeeming aspect of Christ s salvation.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The saving aspect of Christ s salvation: Saving God s elect from God s punishment.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Saving God s elect from the corrupted generation.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Ushering God s elect into a renewed age.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The good land typifying the riches of Christ as the enjoyment of God s elect: The riches of the good land: Water waterbrooks, springs, and fountains.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Food wheat, barley, vines, fig trees, pomegranates, olive trees, milk, and honey: Two kinds of grain wheat and barley.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Four kinds of trees vines, fig trees, pomegranates, and olive trees.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Milk and honey.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Minerals stones, mountains, iron, and copper: Stones and mountains.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Iron and copper.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The enjoyment of the good land: Eliminating the idols and all things related to idolatry.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Being in the place which God chose.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Presenting the riches of the good land as offerings to God and enjoying them with Him.</S>
   </TEXT>
